# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this React + Vite project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Added `@vercel/analytics` v2.0.1 to project dependencies
- Used npm to install the package
- Updated package.json and package-lock.json

### 2. Code Changes

**Modified: task-manager-ui/src/App.jsx**
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the main container div
- This placement ensures analytics tracking is enabled across all views (login, register, tasks, dashboard)

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide (fetched on 2026-03-19):
- Package: @vercel/analytics
- Framework: React
- Integration method: Added Analytics component to the root App component

The Analytics component is placed at the root level to ensure:
- Tracking works across all application views
- No interference with existing application logic
- Minimal code changes while maintaining full functionality

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
✅ No new linting errors introduced (existing warnings were pre-existing)
✅ Dependencies properly updated in package.json and package-lock.json
✅ Analytics component properly imported and rendered

## Next Steps

To complete the setup:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
3. After deployment, analytics data will automatically be collected and visible in the dashboard

## Notes

- The Analytics component is lightweight and won't impact application performance
- Data collection begins automatically after deployment to Vercel
- No additional configuration is required in the code
